## Support

Feature-level support tracking with test script references.

### 23.2 ([tc39.es](https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-typedarray-objects))

| Feature name | Status | Test scripts | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| TypedArray surface area in JS2IL | Incomplete |  | Current implementation is an Int32Array-focused subset rather than the full %TypedArray% constructor/prototype hierarchy. |

### 23.2.2.1 ([tc39.es](https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-%typedarray%.from))

| Feature name | Status | Test scripts | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| %TypedArray%.from / %TypedArray%.of | Not Yet Supported |  | Static %TypedArray% constructor helpers are not implemented. |

### 23.2.3.26 ([tc39.es](https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-%typedarray%.prototype.set))

| Feature name | Status | Test scripts | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| Int32Array.prototype.set(source[, offset]) | Supported with Limitations | [`Int32Array_Set_FromArray_WithOffset.js`](../../../Js2IL.Tests/TypedArray/JavaScript/Int32Array_Set_FromArray_WithOffset.js) | Copies from array-like and Int32Array inputs with offset support; behavior is tailored to Int32Array and does not cover full TypedArray species/buffer edge cases. |

### 23.2.5.1 ([tc39.es](https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-typedarray))

| Feature name | Status | Test scripts | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| Int32Array constructor (length, array-like, typed-array copy subset) | Supported with Limitations | [`Int32Array_Construct_Length.js`](../../../Js2IL.Tests/TypedArray/JavaScript/Int32Array_Construct_Length.js)<br>[`Int32Array_FromArray_CopyAndCoerce.js`](../../../Js2IL.Tests/TypedArray/JavaScript/Int32Array_FromArray_CopyAndCoerce.js) | Supports new Int32Array(length) and selected array-like/list sources with ToInt32-style coercion; full multi-constructor TypedArray model is not implemented. |

### 23.2.5.1.3 ([tc39.es](https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-initializetypedarrayfromarraybuffer))
